  "text": "Army ants (Neivamyrmex spp.), many of which are primarily predators of other ant species, have been recorded preying on T. arizonensis in southern Arizona [CITATION_1] . Our records of Neivamyrmex in the cave are not in proximity to the Jackrabbit Shaft. If N. graciellae does prey on T. arizonensis, it likely occurs outside of the cave proper, in the soil profile. N. leonardi is probably too small a species to successfully predate Trachymyrmex spp.",
